    "authentication_flow": {
      "http_request_flow": [
        "1. HTTP request arrives → contexthandler.Middleware wraps it",
        "2. setRequestContext calls authenticator.Authenticate(ctx, &authn.Request{HTTPRequest: req})",
        "3. The authn service iterates registered clients by priority; APIKey.Test() returns true if Authorization header is non-empty",
        "4. APIKey.Authenticate() calls getTokenFromRequest() → reads 'Authorization: Bearer <token>' or 'Authorization: Basic api_key:<token>'",
        "5. getAPIKey() dispatches: token starts with 'gl' → getFromToken (satokengen.Decode → Hash → GetAPIKeyByHash); otherwise → getFromTokenLegacy (apikeygen.Decode → GetApiKeyByName → IsValid)",
        "6. validateApiKey() checks: Expires (Unix timestamp ≤ now), IsRevoked, OrgID match, ServiceAccountId non-nil and > 0",
        "7. newServiceAccountIdentity() builds Identity{Type: TypeServiceAccount, FetchSyncedUser: true, SyncPermissions: true}",
        "8. Post-auth: authn service syncs the service account user from DB and loads RBAC permissions",
        "9. Hook() fires asynchronously to update last_used_at (throttled to once per 5 minutes)",
        "10. reqContext.SignedInUser is set; IsSignedIn = true",
        "11. Route handler runs; accesscontrol.Middleware(ac)(evaluator) checks RBAC if present"
      ],
      "grpc_request_flow": [
        "1. gRPC request arrives with 'authorization: Bearer <token>' metadata",
        "2. interceptors.authenticator.tokenAuth() extracts and strips the header",
        "3. satokengen.Decode() validates prefix and CRC32 checksum",
        "4. decoded.Hash() → GetAPIKeyByHash() → verifies key exists",
        "5. Checks ServiceAccountId != nil",
        "6. GetSignedInUser() loads the service account user",
        "7. Enforces HasRole(org.RoleAdmin) and !IsDisabled",
        "8. Loads RBAC permissions via AccessControlService.GetUserPermissions",
        "9. Sets user in gRPC context via contextHandler.SetUser"
      ],
      "scope_enforcement_flow": [
        "1. Route is registered with accesscontrol.Middleware(ac)(EvalPermission('datasources:read', 'datasources:uid:' + Parameter(':uid')))",
        "2. On request: scopeInjector resolves Parameter(':uid') from URL params via Go text/template",
        "3. ac.Evaluate(ctx, user, injected) looks up user.Permissions[action] and calls match(userScope, targetScope)",
        "4. match() does wildcard prefix matching: 'datasources:*' matches any 'datasources:…'; exact match otherwise",
        "5. On false: deny() returns HTTP 403 with 'Access denied' JSON body"
      ]
